body:
There are only two differences between BINARY and HEX:
- `ssHeader.str()` and `HexStr(ssHeader)`
- `"application/octet-stream"` vs `"text/plain"`

It could be written a lot more concisely as something like this:
```cpp
case RetFormat::BINARY:
case RetFormat::HEX: {
    CDataStream ssHeader(SER_NETWORK, PROTOCOL_VERSION);
    for (const uint256& header : filter_headers) {
        ssHeader << header;
    }

    std::string header_string = (rf == RetFormat::HEX) ? HexStr(ssHeader) : ssHeader.str();
    std::string content_type = (rf == RetFormat::HEX) ? "text/plain" : "application/octet-stream";
    req->WriteHeader("Content-Type", content_type);
    req->WriteReply(HTTP_OK, header_string);
    return true;
}
```

